---
import Canvas from "../layouts/Canvas.astro";
---

<Canvas title="16 · Dashboard UI — Sardis Canvas" currentId="dashboard">

<section class="hero">
        <span class="eyebrow">Canvas 16 · Product</span>
        <h1>Dashboard UI</h1>
        <p class="hero-lead">
          Forty-three operator pages under <code>apps/dashboard/</code>. Next.js 16 App Router (React 19),
          Tailwind v4, shadcn/ui, monokrom grayscale theme. Built for finance and engineering
          operators to see, approve, and kill agent spend without a support ticket — and nothing
          on the page competes with the data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section" style="padding-top:0; border-top:0;">
        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <span class="callout-title">TL;DR</span>
          The dashboard is the <em>control plane</em>. It does not sign transactions and it does not
          hold private keys. It reads from the same Postgres the API writes to, streams live events
          over SSE, and writes back via the same REST surface that SDKs use — with a human in front
          of every action.
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Stack -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Stack</div>
          <h2>What's running under <code>apps/dashboard/</code>.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            Every dependency here is in <code>apps/dashboard/package.json</code>. No component is
            custom-rolled when shadcn already has one; no icon set outside Phosphor; no gradients;
            no emoji.
          </p>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Concern</th><th>Choice</th><th>Why</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Framework</td><td>Next.js <code>16.2.1</code> (App Router) on React <code>19.2.4</code></td><td>Server Components for the heavy list/detail pages; client islands for live widgets.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Styling</td><td>Tailwind v4 + <code>tw-animate-css</code> + <code>tailwind-merge</code></td><td>Monokrom grayscale tokens, no custom CSS file per page.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Component library</td><td>shadcn/ui (<code>shadcn@4</code>) + Radix primitives</td><td>Owned locally, a11y baked in, no runtime framework.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Icons</td><td><code>@phosphor-icons/react</code></td><td>Monoline, weight-consistent; zero emoji.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Auth</td><td><code>better-auth</code> v1.5 (EdDSA/JWKS) + legacy FastAPI JWT (HS256) dual path</td><td>Passkeys, org roles, and a migration path. Plugins: <code>@better-auth/agent-auth</code>, <code>@better-auth/api-key</code>, <code>@better-auth/passkey</code>, <code>@better-auth/stripe</code>.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Billing</td><td><code>@polar-sh/better-auth</code> + <code>@polar-sh/sdk</code> + <code>stripe</code></td><td>Polar now, Stripe-ready when Atlas entity clears.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Analytics</td><td><code>posthog-js</code></td><td>Funnel + retention on the dashboard itself.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Onboarding tour</td><td><code>driver.js</code> v1.4</td><td>Six-step dark-themed tour on first login.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Charts</td><td><code>recharts</code> v3</td><td>Grayscale palettes, tabular numerals.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Forms</td><td><code>react-hook-form</code> + <code>@hookform/resolvers</code> + <code>input-otp</code></td><td>Schema-validated on client and server.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Toasts</td><td><code>sonner</code></td><td>Low-chrome notifications.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Date</td><td><code>date-fns</code> v4 + <code>react-day-picker</code> v9</td><td>Timezone-safe rollups and range pickers.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Observability</td><td><code>@sentry/nextjs</code> v10</td><td>Client + server error + session replay.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Captcha</td><td><code>@captchafox/react</code>, <code>@marsidev/react-turnstile</code></td><td>Abuse-prevention on sign-up and reset flows.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Support</td><td><code>@intercom/messenger-js-sdk</code></td><td>In-app conversations for on-call customers.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Fonts</td><td>Geist Sans + Geist Mono (self-hosted)</td><td>Linear/Vercel-grade legibility without a license bill.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Route structure -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Route Structure</div>
          <h2>Two kinds of surface: the protected operator app and public flows.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            <code>(dashboard)</code> is a Next.js route group — it applies a shared layout (auth
            guard + sidebar + top bar) without appearing in the URL. <code>/demo</code>,
            <code>/auth/*</code>, and <code>/account/*</code> live outside the group so they render
            without the operator chrome.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="diagram">
          <pre class="mermaid" is:raw>
flowchart TB
    subgraph public[Public / unauth]
      DEMO["/demo"]
      AUTH["/auth/[path]"]
      ACCT["/account/[path]"]
    end

    subgraph dash["(dashboard) group · auth-gated"]
      OV["(overview)/"]
      AG["agents · agents/new · wallets · analytics"]
      PM["mandates · policy-manager · approvals · approval-config · guardrails · counterparties · fallback-rules"]
      SC["kill-switch · evidence · audit-anchors · anomaly-detection · alerts · exceptions"]
      PO["transactions · holds · settlements · reconciliation · invoices · mpp-sessions"]
      ME["merchants · merchants/analytics · checkout-controls"]
      DV["api-keys · api-playground · webhooks · live-events · simulation · workflows"]
      IN["observability · provider-health · go-live · environments · virtual-cards · billing"]
      SU["support · control-center · settings"]
    end

    U["User"] --&gt; AUTH --&gt; dash
    U --&gt; DEMO
          </pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Group: Overview + Agents -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 01 · Overview &amp; Agents</div>
          <h2>Who the agents are and what they're doing.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Route</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Key components</th><th>API routers</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>(dashboard)/(overview)</code></td><td>Org-wide snapshot — active agents, today's spend, last 10 decisions.</td><td>StatCards, SSE event feed, recharts sparkline</td><td><code>me</code>, <code>wallets</code>, <code>transactions</code>, <code>live_events</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>agents</code></td><td>List + filter agents by framework, wallet, last active.</td><td>Command palette filter, virtualized table</td><td><code>agents</code>, <code>groups</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>agents/new</code></td><td>Create agent wizard — pick framework, wallet policy, compliance posture.</td><td>Stepper, react-hook-form</td><td><code>agents</code>, <code>policies</code>, <code>kyc_onboarding</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>wallets</code></td><td>All wallets, balances, chain breakdown, per-wallet mini-policy.</td><td>Table with inline drawer detail</td><td><code>wallets</code>, <code>funding</code>, <code>fx</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>analytics</code></td><td>Usage + spend analytics, per-framework breakdown.</td><td>recharts bar/line/area, date-range picker</td><td><code>usage</code>, <code>spending</code>, <code>transactions</code></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Policies & Mandates -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 02 · Policies &amp; Mandates</div>
          <h2>What agents are allowed to do.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead><tr><th>Route</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Key components</th><th>API routers</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>policy-manager</code></td><td>Browse, edit, version natural-language &amp; structured policies.</td><td>Diff viewer, policy parser preview</td><td><code>policies</code>, <code>spending_policy</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>mandates</code></td><td>Active agent-payment mandates (AP2 / A2A delegation).</td><td>Mandate chain viewer, signature verifier</td><td><code>mandates</code>, <code>ap2</code>, <code>mandate_delegation</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>approvals</code></td><td>Pending human-in-the-loop approval queue.</td><td>Inbox UI with keyboard nav</td><td><code>approvals</code>, <code>approval_service</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>approval-config</code></td><td>Which conditions route to humans (amount, counterparty, risk).</td><td>Rule builder</td><td><code>approvals</code>, <code>policies</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>guardrails</code></td><td>Agent-level guardrails (rate, token, purpose).</td><td>Toggle matrix</td><td><code>guardrails</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>counterparties</code></td><td>Allow/block lists, per-counterparty policy.</td><td>Searchable table + quick-add</td><td><code>counterparties</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>fallback-rules</code></td><td>What happens on policy failure — deny, approve, escalate.</td><td>Decision tree editor</td><td><code>policies</code>, <code>approvals</code></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Security -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 03 · Security &amp; Compliance</div>
          <h2>The red buttons and the audit trail.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead><tr><th>Route</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Key components</th><th>API routers</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>kill-switch</code></td><td>Org-wide or per-agent pause. Primary red-button UI.</td><td>Confirm dialog + countdown</td><td><code>kill_switch</code>, <code>emergency</code>, <code>admin</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>evidence</code></td><td>Export cryptographic evidence bundles for regulators.</td><td>Bundle builder, Merkle proof viewer</td><td><code>evidence</code>, <code>data_export</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>audit-anchors</code></td><td>On-chain anchor status (SardisLedgerAnchor.sol tx feed).</td><td>Tx explorer deeplinks</td><td><code>ledger</code>, <code>anchors</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>anomaly-detection</code></td><td>ML anomaly scores per agent/wallet/day.</td><td>Heatmap, threshold slider</td><td><code>anomaly_detection</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>alerts</code></td><td>Active alerts, ack/resolve, owner assignment.</td><td>Incident board</td><td><code>alerts</code>, <code>monitoring</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>exceptions</code></td><td>Policy-denied + errored operations, with replay.</td><td>Detail drawer + replay button</td><td><code>exceptions</code></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Payments & Ops -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 04 · Payments &amp; Ops</div>
          <h2>Where real-world money movement surfaces.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead><tr><th>Route</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Key components</th><th>API routers</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>transactions</code></td><td>All tx, filterable by wallet/agent/status/chain.</td><td>Virtualized table + detail drawer with tx hash links</td><td><code>transactions</code>, <code>payments</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>holds</code></td><td>Active + released holds (auth / capture / void).</td><td>Action bar: extend, capture, void</td><td><code>holds</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>settlements</code></td><td>Settlement batches — CCTP burn/mint, fiat ACH/SEPA/PIX.</td><td>Batch timeline</td><td><code>settlement</code>, <code>bridge</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>reconciliation</code></td><td>Reconciliation queue items + manual resolve.</td><td>Diff viewer (expected vs. observed)</td><td><code>reconciliation</code>, <code>exceptions</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>invoices</code></td><td>Org invoices + per-agent line items.</td><td>PDF preview, Stripe/Polar links</td><td><code>billing</code>, <code>invoices</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>mpp-sessions</code></td><td>Stripe MPP sessions (Tempo / mainnet).</td><td>Session detail + protocol log</td><td><code>mpp</code>, <code>stripe_connect</code></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Merchants -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 05 · Merchants (Pay with Sardis)</div>
          <h2>Merchant-side of the checkout product.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead><tr><th>Route</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Key components</th><th>API routers</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>merchants</code></td><td>Merchant roster, onboarding state, settlement address.</td><td>Onboarding stepper</td><td><code>merchant</code>, <code>merchant_checkout</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>merchants/analytics</code></td><td>Per-merchant volume, conversion, refund rate.</td><td>Cohort table + recharts area</td><td><code>merchant</code>, <code>checkout</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>checkout-controls</code></td><td>Checkout session controls — allowed origins, checkout links.</td><td>Origin allow-list editor</td><td><code>checkout</code></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Developer -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 06 · Developer</div>
          <h2>Keys, webhooks, and live playground.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead><tr><th>Route</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Key components</th><th>API routers</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>api-keys</code></td><td>Create / rotate / revoke keys (<code>sk_live_</code>, <code>sk_test_</code>, <code>pk_live_</code>).</td><td>Reveal-once input, rotation confirm</td><td><code>api_keys</code>, <code>auth</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>api-playground</code></td><td>In-app REPL for the Sardis API.</td><td>Request builder + JSON diff</td><td>All</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>webhooks</code></td><td>Subscribe / test / inspect webhook deliveries.</td><td>Delivery history + HMAC verifier</td><td><code>webhooks</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>live-events</code></td><td>SSE event tail — live decisions as they happen.</td><td>Virtualized log list</td><td><code>live_events</code>, <code>streaming</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>simulation</code></td><td>Sandbox simulator for policies and payments.</td><td>Scenario form</td><td><code>simulation</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>workflows</code></td><td>Workflow builder surface (n8n / Activepieces tie-ins).</td><td>Block list, trigger preview</td><td><code>workflows</code></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Infra -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 07 · Infra</div>
          <h2>Behind the scenes — providers, environments, billing.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead><tr><th>Route</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Key components</th><th>API routers</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>observability</code></td><td>Sentry bridge, trace links, request-rate panels.</td><td>iframe + trace deep links</td><td><code>monitoring</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>provider-health</code></td><td>External provider heartbeats (Turnkey, Didit, Elliptic, Alchemy, Circle).</td><td>Status grid with last-check timestamps</td><td><code>health</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>go-live</code></td><td>Go-live checklist: KYC, KYB, webhook signing, rate limits, kill switch test.</td><td>Stepper with inline validation</td><td><code>admin</code>, <code>kyc_onboarding</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>environments</code></td><td>Manage live/test/sandbox envs, per-env keys, toggles.</td><td>Env switcher</td><td><code>environments</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>virtual-cards</code></td><td>Stripe Issuing card controls — issue, freeze, cancel.</td><td>Card detail drawer, spend caps</td><td><code>cards</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>billing</code></td><td>Plan, seats, usage meter, invoices, payment method (Polar).</td><td>Plan matrix + Polar session redirect</td><td><code>billing</code></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Support -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 08 · Support &amp; Admin</div>
          <h2>Escape hatches.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead><tr><th>Route</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Key components</th><th>API routers</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>support</code></td><td>In-app Intercom + quick docs + replay-capable ticket creator.</td><td>Intercom widget, replay attach</td><td><code>support</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>control-center</code></td><td>Platform-admin console — cross-tenant ops (internal).</td><td>Role-gated</td><td><code>admin</code>, <code>emergency</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>settings</code></td><td>Org settings — team, roles, branding, retention.</td><td>Sectioned form</td><td><code>me</code>, <code>org</code></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Public -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Group 09 · Public flows</div>
          <h2>Surfaces that render without the operator chrome.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead><tr><th>Route</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>/demo</code></td><td>Unauthenticated demo — try Sardis (sandbox) without signing up.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>/auth/[path]</code></td><td>better-auth catch-all: sign-in, sign-up, forgot, reset, verify, passkey.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>/account/[path]</code></td><td>Account management after login — profile, sessions, security.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Design language -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Design Language</div>
          <h2>Monokrom, tabular, keyboard-first.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            Everything grayscale except rare risk-signal accents (policy-denied red on action; never
            on decoration). Phosphor regular weight, 16/20px. Numerals tabular; sparse grid. A page
            like <code>(overview)/page.tsx</code> is a stack of shadcn <code>Card</code> blocks — no
            dashboards-inside-dashboards, no widget marketplace.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-2">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Themes</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              <code>next-themes</code> drives light/dark; both share information density and
              contrast. No third "brand" theme. Toggle lives in the user menu.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Charts</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              <code>recharts</code> with a single grayscale palette. No pie charts. No background
              gradients. Axis labels in <code>Geist Mono</code>; tabular nums for values.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Keyboard</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              <code>cmdk</code> command palette (⌘K) jumps anywhere; every table supports arrow-key
              row navigation; destructive actions always require confirm-with-type.
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Icons &amp; forbidden lists</div>
            <div class="card-description">
              Phosphor only. No emoji anywhere in-product. No gradients. No drop shadows deeper than
              shadcn's default. No custom one-off components when a primitive already exists.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Onboarding -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Onboarding</div>
          <h2>Six-step driver.js tour.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            Runs once on first login (localStorage flag <code>sardis-tour-seen</code>).
            Dark-themed to match the default dashboard theme. Skippable; restartable from
            <code>settings</code>.
          </p>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Anchor</th><th>Teaches</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>1</td><td>Sidebar</td><td>Core / Policies / Security / Settings organisation.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>2</td><td>Overview stats</td><td>Where today's spend + active-agent count live.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>3</td><td><code>agents/new</code> CTA</td><td>Two-minute path to a working agent.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>4</td><td>Policy-manager tile</td><td>Natural-language → structured policy preview.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>5</td><td>Kill-switch tile</td><td>The red button — how to pause everything.</td></tr>
            <tr><td>6</td><td>API keys</td><td>Where to mint a <code>sk_test_</code> key and start building.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Auth flow -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Auth</div>
          <h2>better-auth + legacy JWT, same session.</h2>
          <p class="text-muted" style="max-width:720px;">
            better-auth handles the dashboard side (sessions, passkeys, roles, API-key plugin,
            Polar billing plugin, agent-auth plugin). A legacy HS256 JWT bridge exists for the
            FastAPI side — the server accepts both and emits a principal to the orchestrator.
            Passkeys land via <code>@better-auth/passkey</code>.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="diagram">
          <pre class="mermaid" is:raw>
sequenceDiagram
    participant B as Browser
    participant NA as Next.js /auth/[path]
    participant BA as better-auth (EdDSA/JWKS)
    participant NP as Neon (ba_* tables)
    participant API as Sardis API (FastAPI)
    participant JWT as Legacy JWT (HS256)

    B-&gt;&gt;NA: POST /auth/sign-in (email+passkey)
    NA-&gt;&gt;BA: authenticate
    BA-&gt;&gt;NP: read / write session
    BA--&gt;&gt;NA: session cookie (EdDSA)
    NA--&gt;&gt;B: 302 /(dashboard)

    B-&gt;&gt;API: request with session cookie
    API-&gt;&gt;BA: verify via JWKS
    API-&gt;&gt;JWT: (fallback) verify HS256 for SDK clients
    API--&gt;&gt;B: response (principal attached)
          </pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Source of truth -->
      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <div class="eyebrow">Source of Truth</div>
          <h2>Files to verify against.</h2>
        </div>
        <table class="data">
          <thead><tr><th>Question</th><th>File</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>What pages exist?</td><td><code>find apps/dashboard/app -name page.tsx</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Deps / versions?</td><td><code>apps/dashboard/package.json</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Overview layout?</td><td><code>apps/dashboard/app/(dashboard)/(overview)/page.tsx</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Policy UI?</td><td><code>apps/dashboard/app/(dashboard)/policy-manager/page.tsx</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Auth wiring?</td><td><code>apps/dashboard/app/auth/[path]/page.tsx</code> + <code>lib/auth.ts</code></td></tr>
            <tr><td>Theme tokens?</td><td><code>apps/dashboard/app/globals.css</code></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <!-- Cross-refs -->
